al service is a positive and critical step toward their greater inclusion and integration into Israeli society. If Israeli policymakers adopt a more communitarian approach to citizenship and to civic national service, it will contribute to building stronger communities and empowering youth, benefitting all.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCitizenshipzIsrael. 0aCitizenship-Israel. 0aNational servicezIsrael. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848096140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438480961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438480961/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles